byline.original: Correspondence of The New-York Daily Times

lead_paragraph: The Cadets of Temperance, a large body of juvenile water-drinkers, are making their annual parade in our city to-day. It is a most gratifying evidence of the spread of correct principles, to know that the Order is rapidly increasing, and that the youthful twig is to bent that it will never yield an manhood to the storms of dissipation.

headline.main: PHILADELPHIA.; Charge of Judge Kane on the Law of Treason, &c.
